                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12884398" author="posix4e" created="Thu, 1 Jul 2010 20:13:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So we want a conf variable to decide between distributed and single node splitlog. We can either do this procedurally, i.e.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;if conf.foo = bar &lt;br/&gt;
do this&lt;br/&gt;
else &lt;br/&gt;
do that&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;or through the so called load class functionality, for instance how we do compression etc.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If we go  load class approach i assume we would have some base hlog and then off of that we could specialize a single split hlog and a distributed split hlog. Any opinions here&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12884399" author="ryanobjc" created="Thu, 1 Jul 2010 20:18:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;do the former, its less susceptible to issues.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12885372" author="tlipcon" created="Mon, 5 Jul 2010 23:54:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It would be nice to refactor the splitLog stuff into a &quot;LogSplitter&quot; class perhaps. I think there might be a patch floating around to do this already? Cosmin, maybe? If that&apos;s the case, we could make it pluggable by class name, which is a bit easier to extend (eg if someone wants to do MapReduceLogSplitter)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But if it happens the first way, that&apos;s fine too.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
